article.headline: Wright St. 60, Detroit 51
article.story: DETROIT -- John David Gardner scored 17 points and Todd Brown added 14 on Friday night to help Wright State to its eighth win in nine games, a 60-51 victory over Detroit. The Raiders (10-8, 4-3 Horizon) led 25-24 at intermission and scored the first seven points of the second half to give themselves a bit of a cushion. The Titans (4-12, 0-7) scored just three points in the first eight minutes of the second half and never got closer than seven points the rest of the night. Scott Grote had 10 points for Wright State, which had 10 steals and scored 12 points off its Detroit's 19 turnovers. Thomas Kennedy had 17 points and 10 rebounds and Eulis Stephens added 12 points for the Titans, who lost their fifth straight and fell for the sixth time in as many meetings with the Raiders.
